  <problem>
    <introduction>
      <p>
        Let <m>\mathbb{Z}_n</m> denote the <term>integers modulo <m>n</m></term> with operation addition.  For example <m>\mathbb{Z}_4</m>
        is the set <m>\{0,1,2,3\}</m> where <m>2+1=3, 3+1=0, 3+2=1</m> etc.. 
      </p>
    </introduction>
    <task>
      <statement>
        <p>
          Pick 4 different <m>n</m>'s at least 2.  Show that <m>\mathbb{Z}_n</m> for your choices for a group.
        </p>
      </statement>
    </task>
    <task>
      <statement>
        <p>
          Prove that <m>\mathbb{Z}_n</m> is always a group.
        </p>
      </statement>
    </task>
  </problem>

  <problem>
    <introduction>
      <p>
        Let <m>D_n</m> denote the symmetries of a regular <m>n</m>-sided polygon, with operation composition.  
        For example in <xref ref="problem-D4"/> describes the symmetries of a regular <m>4</m>-gon ie a square.
      </p>
    </introduction>
    <task>
      <statement>
        <p>
          Pick 3 different <m>n</m>'s at least 3.  Show that <m>D_n</m> for your choices for a group.
        </p>
      </statement>
    </task>
    <task>
      <statement>
        <p>
          Prove that <m>D_n</m> is always a group.
        </p>
      </statement>
    </task>
  </problem>

  <problem>
    <introduction>
