  <problem>
    <statement>
      <p>
        Consider the group <m>\mathbb{Z}_3\times\mathbb{Z}_3\times\mathbb{Z}_3\times\mathbb{Z}_3</m>.  Recall SET.  Let the first entry correspond to number, the second color, the third shading and the fourth shape.  Assign a value to each characteristic.
      </p>
      <p>
        Let a GSET denote a collection of three cards so that their sum is <m>(0,0,0,0)</m>.
      </p>
    </statement>
    <task>
      <p>
        Compare GSETS to SETS.  What collections of cards are SETS but not GSETS?  What are GSETS but not SETS?
      </p>
    </task>
    <task>
      <p>
        Pick a card which corresponds to <m>(0,0,0,0)</m> pick two other cards <m>a, b</m> which are not inverses of each other.  What is the subgroup generated by these two cards and what are their corresponding cards?

      </p>
    </task>
    <task>
      <p>
        Remember when we conjectured that any 3 cards which don't form a SET would generate a plane?  Now prove it.
      </p>
    </task>

  </problem>



  
